  abstract = {Context. Proto-planetary disks are thought to provide the initial 
environment for planetary system formation. The dust and gas
distribution and its evolution with time is one of the key elements in
the process. Aims: We attempt to characterize the radial
distribution of dust in disks around a sample of young stars from an
observational point of view, and, when possible, in a model-independent
way, by using parametric laws. Methods: We used the IRAM PdBI
